org.usb4java

Class ConfigDescriptor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.usb4java.ConfigDescriptor

  • public final class ConfigDescriptor
extends Object
    A structure representing the standard USB configuration descriptor. This descriptor is documented in section 9.6.3 of the USB 3.0 specification. All multiple-byte fields are represented in host-endian format.
    Author:
    Klaus Reimer (k@ailis.de)

    • Constructor Summary

      Constructors 
      Constructor and Description
      ConfigDescriptor()
      Constructs a new config descriptor which can be passed to the LibUsb.getConfigDescriptor(Device, byte, ConfigDescriptor) method.
